# Frontend Patterns

## Architecture

Two dashboards:
- `app.js` + `index.html`: full-featured dashboard (scan, approve, portfolio, settings, SEC analysis)
- `simple.js` + `simple.html`: lightweight scan + diagnostics UI for external/embed use

## State Management

Single top-level mutable object — no framework:
```javascript
const state = { latestSignals: [], approvingTradeId: null, ... };
```

## API Calls

Use the shared `api` object (do NOT use raw `fetch`):
```javascript
const { ok, data, error } = await api.get("/api/endpoint");
const result = await api.post("/api/action", { body: payload });
```

- `api.request()` handles: `AbortController` timeout (90s default), `Authorization: Bearer` from `getApiAccessToken()`, `X-API-Key` from localStorage when `publicConfig.api_key_required`, JSON parsing, error extraction
- Auth: Supabase access token via `getApiAccessToken()`; cookie-based session as fallback

## DOM Updates

- `document.getElementById(id)` for element access
- `el.innerHTML` for rich content, `el.textContent` for plain text
- `el.classList.add/remove/toggle` for state-driven styling
- `document.createElement` for dynamic list/table construction
- Lazy loading: `IntersectionObserver` on `[data-lazy-api]` elements

## Config

Fetch `/api/public-config` at startup for client-side feature flags:
```javascript
const cfg = await api.get("/api/public-config");
state.publicConfig = cfg.data;
```

## Conventions

- No build step — vanilla ES6 modules
- Template literals for HTML fragments
- Error display via toast/banner pattern using `showError(msg)` or inline `.error` elements
- Numeric formatting helpers: `fmtPct()`, `fmtUSD()`, `safeNum()`
